Chapter 2

The next morning, Simba set out to patrol his territory. As he walked through the grass, he noticed a group of hyenas lurking at the edge of his pride's hunting grounds.

Simba knew that the hyenas were always looking for an opportunity to steal his prey, and he could not allow them to encroach on his territory. With a mighty roar, Simba charged at the hyenas, his massive paws pounding the ground as he ran.

The hyenas scattered, and Simba stood victorious over his territory once again. But as he looked out over the savannah, he realized that this was only the beginning of the challenges that lay ahead.
